criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. diagnosed with mild, moderate or severe TBI at least six months before enrolment in
             study, based on the World Health Organization criteria [16]: Mild: length of loss or
             altered level of consciousness (LOC) 0-30 minutes, Glasgow Coma Scale (GCS) score
             13-15/15, negative or positive brain imaging (CT-Scan or MRI), post-traumatic amnesia
             (PTA) duration <24 hrs; Moderate: LOC 30 min-24 hrs, GCS score 9-12, positive brain
             imaging, PTA duration 1-14 days; Severe: LOC >24 h, GCS score 3-8, positive brain
             imaging, PTA duration >2 weeks [16];

          2. post-traumatic amnesia period must be already resolved;

          3. aged at least 55 years;

          4. fluent in French (speaking, understanding, reading).

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. previously received or receiving another specific or direct cognitive intervention
             focusing on similar or identical cognitive functions;

          2. diagnosis or documented clinical impressions of dementia (medical files) or Montreal
             Cognitive Assessment score lower than 20;

          3. diagnosis of an active psychiatric condition;

          4. consumption of alcohol (drinking 5 or more drinks on the same occasion on each of 5 or
             more days weekly in the past 30 days), or consuming illicit drugs.
